Kraemer Says Quake Won’t Prompt Recession, Euro am Sonntag Says

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-03-14T17:06:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/kraemer-says-quake-won-t-prompt-recession-euro-am-sonntag-says.html
  Commerzbank AG (CBK)  doesn’t see the
global economy falling back into recession because of the
earthquake in  Japan ,  Euro am Sonntag  said, citing an interview
with Joerg Kraemer, the chief economist of the German lender.  The global economy “won’t change its course” because of
the events in Japan, Kraemer said, according to Euro am Sonntag.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
